<p>The <strong>Fun Hypothesis Tester</strong> (now called the
<strong>Framing Hypothesis Tester</strong>) tests whether LLMs perform
better when prompts are framed in different styles.</p>
<h2 id="the-hypothesis">The Hypothesis</h2>
<blockquote>
<p>Does asking Claude “Let’s have fun figuring this out together!”
produce better answers than a dry, neutral prompt?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Or more generally: <strong>Does prompt framing affect response
quality?</strong></p>
<h2 id="how-it-works">How It Works</h2>
<pre><code>┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Session A: Send raw prompt → Get Response A                │
│  Session B: Transform prompt with framing → Get framed prompt│
│  Session C: Send framed prompt → Get Response B             │
│  Session D: Blind judge rates Response A                    │
│  Session E: Blind judge rates Response B                    │
│  Compare scores statistically                               │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘</code></pre>
<p>Each session is independent (no context leakage).</p>
